subSubSection.paragraph:
FEMALE (
paralectotype
, data extracted from Birula, 1911a). Very similar to male, sexual dimorphism evident by: 
1)
size slightly larger; 
2)
metasoma somewhat less slender; 
3)
tergites I–VI with median carina more strongly and regularly developed; 
4)
pectines with consistently lower tooth count (20/20); 
5)
tibial spur highly reduced on leg III.
